                    <msContents>
                        <summary/>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                        <locus from="2r" to="49r"/>
                         <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4002Salotz">Ṣalot za-Muse</title>
                         <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                         <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                           ንነግረክሙ፡ አኃውየ፡ መግረሬ፡ ፀር፡ ወመድኅነ፡ ሙሴ፡ እምእደ፡ ፈርዖን፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ሙሴ፨
                           </incipit>
                           <note>The prayer is divided into four parts that
                           begin on <locus target="#2r"/>, <locus target="#28v"/>,
                         <locus target="#31r"/>, <locus target="#44v"/>, resp. The name of the scribe, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13744Giyorgis">Giyorgis</persName>,
                         appears in the concluding supplication on <locus target="#49r"/>. C. Conti Rossini suggests
                       that this specific version of the text may be of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/ETH1274Betaes">Beta ʾƎsrāʾel</persName> origin.</note>
                            </msItem>

                         <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <locus from="50r"/>
                            <locus target="#1v"/>
                            <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2393tabiba">Ṭabiba ṭabibān</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                           <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                             </incipit>
                             <note>According to C. Conti Rossini, the text ends on
                               <locus target="#1v"/> due to the mistake of the scribe;
                               his name, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13744Giyorgis">Giyorgis</persName>, is
                               mentioned in the explicit.
                               The manuscript has not been used in the edition in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/TQ2NBVAC"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1866Chrestomathia"/><title level="m">Chrestomathia Aethiopica edita et glossario explanata</title><editor><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Christian Friedrich August</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Dillmann</t:surname></editor><pubPlace>Lipsiae</pubPlace><publisher>T. O. Weigel</publisher><date>1866</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_V2XoxZmczckC</note></bibl>.</note>
                         </msItem>
                      </msContents>

